text: The 2018–19 Austrian Cup was the national cup in Austrian football. The champions of the cup earned a place in the 2019–20 Europa League and would have begun play in the Group stage. Sixty–four clubs participated in this season's cup competition. Sturm Graz were the defending champions. == First round == Thirty–two first round matches were played between 20 and 22 July 2018. == Second round == Fifteen second round matches were played 25 September 2018. ==Third round== The eight third round matches were played on 30 October 2018. == Quarter-finals == The four quarter-finals matches were played from 15 to 17 February 2019. ==Semi-finals== == Final == {| style="font-size: 90%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" GK 1 Alexander Walke (c) RB 22 Stefan Lainer CB 6 Jérôme Onguéné CB 15 André Ramalho LB 25 Patrick Farkas MF 42 Xaver Schlager MF 8 Diadie Samassékou MF 16 Zlatko Junuzovic MF 13 Hannes Wolf FW 9 Mu'nas Dabbur FW 21 Fredrik Gulbrandsen Substitutes: Substitutes: Substitutes: GK 1 Cican Stankovic CB 5 Albert Vallci FW 11 Smail Prevljak MF 14 Dominik Szoboszlai MF 18 Takumi Minamino FW 20 Patson Daka CM 45 Enock Mwepu Manager: Manager: Manager: Marco Rose Marco Rose Marco Rose Marco Rose == References == == Other websites == * soccerway.com Category:Austrian Cup Category:2018–19 in European football Category:2010s in Austrian sport
